<dl id="n32050d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n32" href="#n32050d">N32 (VI.B.23)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n32all.htm#n32050d"> 50(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> gangetic doab</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font size="-1">HINDOSTANI</font> &mdash; the name given by Europeans to an Indo-Aryan dialect (whose home is in the upper <mark>Gangetic Doab</mark> and near the city of Dehli), which, owing to political causes, has become the great <i>lingua franca</i> of modern India. <small> &ldquo;HINDOSTANI&rdquo; <a name="EBHI" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBHI"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 479(a)</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
